1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,079
A mathematical structure M is defined algebraically as follows.

2
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:07,626
There is a set M, called the domain of the structure.

3
00:00:07,666 --> 00:00:11,217
So, again for the theory of arithmetic, this would just be the

4
00:00:11,317 --> 00:00:14,573
set of natural numbers. For a graph this would be the set

5
00:00:14,673 --> 00:00:18,694
of vertices, etc. This is the domain over which the quantifiers range.

6
00:00:18,733 --> 00:00:21,791
So in arithmetic, when we say for all x there

7
00:00:21,891 --> 00:00:24,458
exists a y such that x is less than y,

8
00:00:24,533 --> 00:00:27,831
the quantifiers range over the natural numbers and this says

9
00:00:27,931 --> 00:00:30,493
that for all numbers, there is a bigger number,

10
00:00:30,533 --> 00:00:33,860
whereas in the theory of graphs, the quantifiers range over

11
00:00:33,960 --> 00:00:36,532
the set of vertices in the graph, if we change

12
00:00:36,632 --> 00:00:39,727
the less than relation to the graph edge relation, this

13
00:00:39,827 --> 00:00:42,632
expresses that all vertices have an outgoing edge.

14
00:00:42,666 --> 00:00:45,633
Then we have a set of constant symbols, function

15
00:00:45,733 --> 00:00:49,018
symbols and relation symbols specific to this theory.

16
00:00:49,133 --> 00:00:51,989
The bridge between the syntax and the semantics is

17
00:00:52,089 --> 00:00:55,240
given by an interpretation function, which is a special

18
00:00:55,340 --> 00:00:58,019
map, sending each symbol to its interpretation,

19
00:00:59,066 --> 00:01:02,571
such that constant symbols are mapped to elements in the domain,

20
00:01:02,666 --> 00:01:06,406
function symbols are mapped to functions in the structure,

21
00:01:06,533 --> 00:01:11,631
and relation symbols to subsets of the domain.

22
00:01:11,733 --> 00:01:16,436
Where functions can be seen as tuples, where inputs are mapped uniquely to

23
00:01:16,536 --> 00:01:20,850
an output. For example, the addition function will map to the set of

24
00:01:20,950 --> 00:01:24,354
all possible triples a, b, c, where a plus b equals c.

25
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:29,068
Similarly, relation symbols will be mapped to all tuples satisfying the

26
00:01:29,168 --> 00:01:33,365
axioms imposed on the relation symbol. For example the less than

27
00:01:33,465 --> 00:01:37,328
relation in the theory of arithmetic, will map to all pairs

28
00:01:37,428 --> 00:01:39,477
a, b such that a is less than b.

29
00:01:39,533 --> 00:01:41,425
This is a bit of a contrived map, but

30
00:01:41,525 --> 00:01:44,118
this is our bridge between the mechanical world of

31
00:01:44,218 --> 00:01:47,080
syntax, where the symbols have no inherent meaning, and

32
00:01:47,180 --> 00:01:50,796
the intuitive world of semantics where mathematical structures exist.

33
00:01:50,866 --> 00:01:53,790
Finally, we need a variable assignment, which will map the

34
00:01:53,890 --> 00:01:56,762
set of free variables to specific elements in the domain.

35
00:01:56,862 --> 00:01:59,838
To motivate this, we show how formulas with free variables,

36
00:01:59,938 --> 00:02:03,592
serve a completely different purpose to formulas without free variables.

37
00:02:03,666 --> 00:02:07,232
Where a free variable is one which is not bounded by

38
00:02:07,332 --> 00:02:11,179
a quantifier. For example, there exists an x such that x

39
00:02:11,279 --> 00:02:14,916
plus x equals y. Here x is bounded by the existential

40
00:02:15,016 --> 00:02:18,299
quantifier and so it is not free, but y is free.

41
00:02:18,333 --> 00:02:22,543
Formulas without free variables, such as 1 plus 1 equals 2, or for all

42
00:02:22,643 --> 00:02:26,607
x there exists y where x is greater than y are known as sentences,

43
00:02:26,707 --> 00:02:31,349
and they make a claims about the structure in question, which are either true

44
00:02:31,449 --> 00:02:35,906
or false in the structure. Formulas with free variables, such as x is less

45
00:02:36,006 --> 00:02:39,416
than y, or there exists an x such that x plus x equals y,

46
00:02:39,516 --> 00:02:44,034
are sometimes true and sometimes false, depending on what x and y refer to.

47
00:02:44,134 --> 00:02:47,359
Formulas with free variables are used for definitions.

48
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:52,987
For example, in the structure of the natural numbers, this formula defines the set

49
00:02:53,087 --> 00:02:57,495
of even numbers, since it is true if and only if we instantiate y

50
00:02:57,595 --> 00:03:01,518
by an even number. So, we can define E equals the set of y

51
00:03:01,618 --> 00:03:05,402
such that there exists an x such that x plus x equals y.

52
00:03:05,466 --> 00:03:09,252
So, a mathematical structure is defined as the pair M, Phi,

53
00:03:09,352 --> 00:03:12,085
where M is as before, and Phi is a map from

54
00:03:12,185 --> 00:03:16,102
the free variables in the formulas to elements in the domain.

55
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:19,664
Now we can define the satisfaction relation, which is

56
00:03:19,764 --> 00:03:22,891
the definition of truth in the semantical world.

57
00:03:22,933 --> 00:03:27,587
So, when we say 1 plus 2 equals 3, we check whether the terms

58
00:03:27,687 --> 00:03:32,341
1 plus 2 and 3 evaluate to the same element in the structure.

59
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:34,337
On the right hand side, we simply map 3

60
00:03:34,437 --> 00:03:36,949
to its interpretation, which is just the number 3.

61
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,700
On the left we have a function term, so we map the

62
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:44,292
components to their interpretations, and then evaluate the result of the function.

63
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:48,308
Similar for other atomic formulas, such as 2 plus 3 is less than

64
00:03:48,408 --> 00:03:52,317
4 times 3. We evaluate the terms on each side, and check whether

65
00:03:52,417 --> 00:03:56,577
the result exists in the subset of pairs of numbers in the relation.

66
00:03:56,666 --> 00:04:01,228
Then, for boolean combinations, the definition of truth is given recursively as we

67
00:04:01,328 --> 00:04:04,526
would expect. So phi and psi is true in a structure if and

68
00:04:04,626 --> 00:04:08,165
only if both phi and psi individually are true in the structure.

69
00:04:08,266 --> 00:04:14,348
For the quantifiers, an expression for all x phi x evaluates to true, if no

70
00:04:14,448 --> 00:04:20,365
matter which value we choose for x, it turns out to be true. For example,

71
00:04:20,465 --> 00:04:25,475
for all x, x plus 1 squared equals x squared plus 2x plus 1 is

72
00:04:25,575 --> 00:04:29,926
true of all natural numbers, and so will be true in N.

